ent itself will consist of. What we do know is that players who complete the event will be able to earn Black Widow's "Mrs. Barnes" series costume rewards, free of charge. Devs also shared that the Galacta's Cosmic Adventure Event will begin on Friday, March 7 at 1 AM PT / 4 AM ET and end on Friday, April 11 at 1:59 AM PT / 4:59 AM ET. Players will likely need to complete a series of in-game challenges to unlock the cosmetic rewards, but given the lack of details in the patch notes, it's possible the event may consist of other activities as well.</p><p dir="ltr">The real star of the latest Marvel Rivals update is a <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/new-marvel-rivals-event-will-let-you-unleash-chaos-as-an-entire-team-of-cloned-heroes/1100-6529857/">new game mode called Clone Rumble</a>. Clone Rumble is exactly what it sounds like: A game mode that allows players to form a team consisting entirely of the same hero. It's looking like Clone Rumble is a limited-time mode, as NetEase included a Clone Rumble schedule in the patch notes. Clone Rumble mode will be available during the following dates and times:</p><ul><li dir="ltr">Friday, March 7 at 1 AM PT / 4 AM ET - Monday, March 10 at 2 AM PT / 5 AM ET</li><li dir="ltr">Friday, March 14 at 2 AM PT / 5 AM ET - Monday, March 17 at 2 AM PT / 5 AM ET</li><li dir="ltr">Friday, March 21 at 2 AM PT / 5 AM ET - Monday, March 24 at 2 AM PT / 5 AM ET</li></ul><p>Keep scrolling for a detailed look at the version 20250307 patch notes (which are listed in full below) or check them out via <a href="https://www.marvelrivals.com/gameupdate/20250304/41548_1215931.html" rel="nofollow ">the official Marvel Rivals website</a>.</p><h2>Patch Notes</h2><h3>Optimizations</h3><p>1. Improved the Human Torch's Lord Proficiency avatar reward.</p><p>2. Added a voice enhancement setting for the microphone.</p><p>3. You can now report those who leave matches prematurely via the menu while still in a match.</p><h3>Fixes</h3><h4>All Platforms</h4><h4>General</h4><p>1. Fixed an issue where switching from a Proficiency Deluxe Avatar back to the standard Avatar required a re-login to take effect.</p><p>2. Resolved an issue where other players viewing a career profile would not immediately see the latest scores added after reaching maximum proficiency with a hero. A re-login was required for the changes to take effect.</p><p>3. Corrected the blocklist full notification, which mistakenly stated that the friends list was full.</p><h4>Maps and Modes</h4><p>1. Fixed several terrain issues that could cause characters to become stuck or clip into strange areas.</p><p>2. Resolved various problems with broken collisions, floating objects, etc.</p><p>3. Addressed multiple map sound effect issues.</p><h4>Heroes</h4><p>1. Loki's Disappearing Act: Fixed an issue where Loki's UI would vanish after he transformed. The God of Mischief can now keep his tricks visible!</p><p>2. Human Torch's Meteor Mishap: Resolved a glitch where the Human Torch's Flaming Meteor ability could sometimes trap hit enemies inside walls. Now, foes will feel the burn, not the barrier!</p><p>3. Persistent Pyro-Prison: Fixed an issue that the Human Torch's Pyro-Prison wouldn't promptly disappear upon his defeat. No more lingering flames!</p><p>4. Loki's Blessing Blunder: Fixed a problem where if Loki and his doppelganger placed Regeneration Domains that overlapped and Loki walked over the overlapped area, then back into his own Regeneration Domain, it would lose its healing effect. Now, the trickster can heal without a hitch!</p><p>5. Punisher's Missile Mayhem: Addressed a rare issue where the Punisher's Ultimate Ability would sometimes continue to detect enemies and fire missiles during network disruptions. The Punisher's firepower is now accurate, even in chaos!</p><p>6. Hela's Knockback Kinks: Resolved an inconsistency where Hela would sometimes be launched up after unleashing her Ultimate Ability. The Goddess of Death will now fly firm to rain destruction her foes!</p><p>7. Wolverine's Leap of Faith: Fixed a quirk where characters launched up by Wolverine's Ultimate Ability would sometimes exhibit exaggerated jumping abilities. The mutant's effect is now properly contained!</p><p>8. Jeff's Ice Surprise: Corrected a bug where when the Team-Up Ability is active, Jeff the Land Shark could launch Frozen Spitballs that exceed expectations via certain actions. The aquatic cutie's attacks are now as intended!</p><p>9. Hela's Vehicle Visibility: Fixed an issue where after Hela releases her Ultimate Ability, sometimes she may not be immediately detected when near the mission vehicle. Now her presence will be felt.</p><p>10. Adam's Ultimate Energy Fail: Resolved a problem where if Adam Warlock's Ultimate Ability failed in certain areas (like cliff edges), 50% energy wouldn't be returned. The hero's energy is now properly restored!</p><p>11. Peni Parker's Positioning Predicament: Fixed a positioning issue that could sometimes occur when Peni was hit by Namor's Ultimate Ability. The mech pilot is now perfectly aligned for battle!</p><h4>PC</h4><p>1. Fixed an issue where some graphics cards couldn't enable Intel XeSS.</p><h4>Console</h4><p>1. Fixed an issue where after modifying the mapping of the controller's L3 button, the chat window could not be opened on the results screen.</p><p>2. Resolved a rare issue on PlayStation where Wolverine's Rage Uncaged trophy sometimes wouldn't unlock.</p>






